<COREF ID="82" TYPE="IDENT">Michael Gould</COREF> states in Surrealism and the Cinema , `` If <COREF ID="83" TYPE="IDENT">the vision revealed</COREF> is too much for the rational mind to absorb -LRB- too intense , too threatening , too ' real ' -RRB- yet can not be rejected , then <COREF ID="83" TYPE="IDENT">it</COREF> leaves the consciousness and comes to exist on a sublime level as pure surrealism '' -LRB- 13 -RRB- .
